HEADWORD: Flatfish
<hw>Flat"fish`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any fish of the family <fam>Pleuronectid⟦ae⟧</fam>; esp., the
winter flounder (<spn>Pleuronectes Americanus</spn>). The flatfishes
have the body flattened, swim on the side, and have eyes on one side, as
the flounder, turbot, and halibut. See <er>Flounder</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

